2025-11-06 | Maximum Subarray Sum with Length Divisible by K

Problem Statement  
You are given an integer array `nums` and an integer `k`.
Return the **maximum subarray sum** among all subarrays whose length is divisible by **k**.


Approach / Explanation  
1. Prefix Sum + Remainder Buckets  
Let `prefix[i]` = sum of first `i` elements.
For any subarray `nums[l..r]`:
sum = prefix[r + 1] - prefix[l]
Length = (r - l + 1)
We want:
(r - l + 1) % k == 0  
→ r % k == (l - 1) % k  
→ prefix-index remainder matches

2. Strategy  
For each remainder class `mod = i % k`, we keep:
- The **minimum prefix sum** seen so far for that remainder.
- Then use it to compute the **maximum possible subarray sum ending at i**.

Reason:  
If prefix[j] and prefix[i] have the same remainder,  
then subarray (j .. i-1) has length divisible by k.

3. Algorithm  
Maintain:
- `prefix = 0`
- `best[0..k-1]` = smallest prefix sum seen for each remainder
- Initialize all best[] = +infinity  
- best[0] = 0  (empty prefix sum)

For each index i:
- prefix += nums[i]
- r = (i+1) % k
- candidate = prefix - best[r]
- Update answer with candidate
- best[r] = min(best[r], prefix)

4. Complexity  
• Time: O(n)  
• Space: O(k)


SOLUTION:
#include <bits/stdc++.h>
using namespace std;

class Solution {
public:
    long long maxSubarraySumDivK(vector<int>& nums, int k) {
        long long prefix = 0;
        long long ans = LLONG_MIN;

        vector<long long> best(k, LLONG_MAX);
        best[0] = 0;  // base case

        for (int i = 0; i < nums.size(); i++) {
            prefix += nums[i];
            int r = (i + 1) % k;

            // Check if we can form a subarray ending here
            if (best[r] != LLONG_MAX) {
                ans = max(ans, prefix - best[r]);
            }

            // Update minimum prefix for this remainder
            best[r] = min(best[r], prefix);
        }

        return ans;
    }
};
